    "summary": "Marcel is an enthusiastic and customer-oriented security professional who operates on a senior level. He has extensive experience in advising clients in the field of Security Risk & Crisis Management. He has gained this experience in various positions in both the government and the private sector.\n\nHe is always looking for ways to further develop his knowledge and skills. In addition to his work experience, he obtained a Bachelor\u2019s degree in Management, Economics and Law as well as a Master\u2019s degree in Security and Risk Management from Leicester University. In addition, he took several training courses on (travel) security, terrorism, and investigations. Marcel also spends time on self-reflection and personal development.\n\nAs he has worked for many years in an international environment, he has a proven ability in building and maintaining a network in a multicultural environment. He has strong advisory skills and communication skills, at different levels. He is alert and sharp-witted and therefore he often sees opportunities to help others.\n\nMarcel enjoys working in a challenging, changing and international environment. Because of his flexible and positive attitude he can adapt well to new situations. He likes to build things from scratch. This he showed in his role as Security Liaison Officer (National Security), where he set up a large and effective network within the international organisations (European Union, United Nations, and NATO) in a short period of time. Marcel enjoys helping to increase the collective security awareness by providing security awareness briefings on terrorism and espionage.\n\nMarcel is registered as a \u2018Register Security Expert\u2019 (RSE, a Dutch security standard) and certified for the United Nations\u2019 \u2018Security Certification Programme\u2019 (SCP). Additionally, he has obtained the official SVPB diploma \u2018Private Investigator\u2019.",
